definition[0]: to be sold in larger quantities than something else
example[0]: It may outsell his previous novels.
definition[1]: to sell more goods or products than a competitor
example[1]: Australia now outsells the US in wines.
definition[2]: to be sold in larger quantities than another product of the same type
example[2]: Chardonnay outsells other white wines by a huge margin.
definition[3]: to sell more products than a competitor
example[3]: The company now outsells its rivals in this market.
